      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DELUCE (4) showed good speed and was handy until they straightened but tired and finished a well-beaten third at his first run back over this distance at Nowra. Will tighten up following that hit-out and looks hard to beat in the small field. STRIKE A POSE (3) is a Yes Yes Yes three-year-old on debut for the Maher stable. Has been to the trials four times since August so will have some race smarts. Half-brother to Group 2 winner Konasana who should acquit himself well. STAR HALF (2) is a first starter for the Hawkes camp. By Zoustar from a Flying Spur mare. Hasn't set the world on fire at the trials but he does find a soft race to kick things off. SUDDEN STRIKE (10) led but just failed to hang on in a weak maiden over 1300m at Orange recently. Might be hard to catch coming back a little in trip. TIARA GAGA (7) debuts. Hasn't shown much at the trials but all five siblings to race are winners so she might have something to offer.",
